abstract: Leaders of Russia, Ukraine, France and Germany agree to continue attempts to end fighting in eastern Ukraine, saying cease-fire agreement will not be fully adhered to by Dec 31 deadline
lead_paragraph: The leaders of Russia, Ukraine, France and Germany called for the Minsk peace agreement to be carried out in full in 2016.

headline.main: World Leaders Agree to Extend Efforts to End Ukraine Conflict
headline.print_headline: Europe; Ukraine: A New Push for Peace
